      with medieval Neumes and notation, can Sibelius do this?
      \ldots\\

      A: Sibelius cannot do it.  You might be interested in software
      called "Gregorio".
    \end{block}
    (Quelle: Forum unter \url{www.sibelius.com}; Datum der Beiträge
    ohne Jahreszahl, offenbar nach 2014)
    %Source: http://www.sibelius.com/cgi-bin/helpcenter/chat/chat.pl?com=thread&start=679201&groupid=3&&guest=1
  }
  \item<3-> {\color<3>{blue} $\Rightarrow$ offenbar bislang keine
    Unterstützung für Neumen oder Ligaturen}
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{Capella}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item<2->[] {\color<2>{blue}
    \begin{block}{Zitat}
      Five music fonts are provided with capella.  \ldots Plainsong
      scores using neumes can be produced by pasting individual neumes
      in place of modern notes.
    \end{block}
    (Quelle: \url{capellasoftware.com/features/}, abgerufen am
